@node eplay "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "Angliant" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher with at least 8 colours.

                             How to play?

  The game consists of a game board where there are a number of
tiles that have 90 degrees angles on them. Positions that do not
have any tiles are shown with small square dots. An 'X' shape is
placed on a starting tile and the exit tile is located on a
coloured square. The starting tile and exit tiles are generally
placed at the opposite ends from each other on the game board.

  To rotate a tile that contains an angle, simply click on it. That
tile, as well as its angle, will rotate clockwise, by 90 degrees.
If you click on a position marked by a small square dot, nothing
will happen.

  The X shape will move when only one angle is connected with the
angle the X shape is located on. When it gets to the exit tile, the
game board is completed...

  Have fun!

OPTIONS:
-------

-New Game button: To restart a game board. Note that all the moves
                  you have made on the game board will be added up
                  until you complete it...

-Colour button:   To change the colour of the 'X' shape, as well
                  as the exit tile.

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

